<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-07T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-07T21:00:00-05:00" n="907" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d907">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/2454: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-08T09:00:00+07:00">April 8,
                                    1941—9 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received April 8—5:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>My April 5, noon. Dr. Tuan Mao-lan<note n="95" xml:id="d907fn1">Senior
                                Secretary in the Chinese Ministry for Foreign Affairs.</note> of the
                            Foreign Office called on me on the evening of April 7 and said that
                            since it is not clear what procedure will be adopted for selection of
                            Chinese members of the proposed provisional council he had been
                            instructed to see me and make the following oral statement on behalf
                            Minister for Foreign Affairs. (See my April 8, 10 a.m.<note n="96" xml:id="d907fn2">
                                <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note>)</p>
                        <p>Sent to Shanghai, repeated to Department and Peiping.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>